🧠 Interview Cheat Sheet
Deployment
"I want 5 Pods."

Kubernetes maintains 5 Pods, regardless of how many nodes exist (as long as there is enough capacity).

DaemonSet
"I want one Pod on every node."

If there are:

3 nodes → 3 Pods
10 nodes → 10 Pods
100 nodes → 100 Pods

📋 DaemonSet Summary
        Feature                 	DaemonSet
------------------------------------------------------------------------ 
 Purpose                        	One Pod per eligible node
 Uses replicas?                  	❌ No
 Automatically scales with nodes?	✅ Yes
 Common uses                    	Logging, Monitoring, Security Agents
 Examples                       	Fluent Bit, Prometheus Node Exporter, Datadog Agent, Falco

